@Node "History" "UMSMailStat.guide/History"
@Toc "Main"

History
*******

     v1.24 (7.9.97)

        @{b}*@{ub} oops, when the GROUP pattern also covered the mails, using
          GROUPSIZES would stop the program (reported by Wolfgang von
          Hansen)

        @{b}*@{ub} the global stats now allow for numbers with up to 10 digits,
          so sizes greater 10 MB can be displayed. (reported by
          Wolfgang von Hansen)

     v1.23 (9.7.97)

        @{b}*@{ub} new option @{"GROUPSIZES" Link "GROUPSIZES"} (as requested by Wolfgang von Hansen)

        @{b}*@{ub} a progressbar is now also displayed while scanning the
          grouplist

     v1.22 (2.6.97)

        @{b}*@{ub} Bugfix: large data could crash UMSMailStat during listoutput
          (thanks to Michael Prix for reporting).

     v1.21 (11.8.96)

        @{b}*@{ub} new option @{"SORTBY" Link "SORTBY"} (inspired by a request from Rene Laederach)

        @{b}*@{ub} new option @{"NOHEADER" Link "NOHEADER"} (as requested by Luc Gibert)

        @{b}*@{ub} when using @{"NOSUBJECTS" Link "NOSUBJECTS & NOUSERS"} and/or @{"NOUSERS" Link "NOSUBJECTS & NOUSERS"} the corresponding list
          will not be sorted any more as it's not necessary."

        @{b}*@{ub} reformatted the "most bytes" statistics and also introduced
          "fewest bytes" statistics.

        @{b}*@{ub} converted the documentation to TexInfo (finally :-)

     v1.20 (23.4.96)

        @{b}*@{ub} new option @{"FOLDER" Link "FOLDER"} (as requested by Matthias Scheler)

        @{b}*@{ub} new option @{"TONAME" Link "TONAME"} (as requested by Luc Gibert and Rene
          Laederach)

     v1.19 (4.11.95)

        @{b}*@{ub} reimplemented CTRL-C break-handling. This time more safe :-)
          (has been removed in v1.11)

     v1.18 (16.8.95)

        @{b}*@{ub} @{"NOSUBJECTS" Link "NOSUBJECTS & NOUSERS"} and @{"NOUSERS" Link "NOSUBJECTS & NOUSERS"} options (as requested by Luc Gibert)

        @{b}*@{ub} french documentation included (many thanks to Luc Gibert!)

     v1.17 (13.6.95)

        @{b}*@{ub} fixed a nasty bug that has been lurking in @{"REALBYTES" Link "REALBYTES"} since
          v1.09.  UMSMailStat had problems with mails larger than 32767
          bytes, now we're able to handle 2 GB messages (if you got the
          mem for it :-D ). Thanks to Luc Gibert for finding this bug!

     v1.16 (18.4.95)

        @{b}*@{ub} french catalog included. Big THANK YOU to Luc Gibert! :-)

        @{b}*@{ub} new options @{"QUOTECHECK" Link "QUOTECHECK"} and @{"QUOTECHARS" Link "QUOTECHARS"} and variables
          @{"UMSMailStat.Quote.Chars" Link "UMSMailStat.Quote.Chars"} and
          @{"UMSMailStat.Quote.CheckFirstNChars" Link "UMSMailStat.Quote.CheckFirstNChars"} for generation of
          statictics about the "quoting habits" of the authors (as
          requested by Luc Gibert).

        @{b}*@{ub} changed the way the progressmeter is printed. (as requested
          by Ralf Garbade)

        @{b}*@{ub} revised the documentation.

     v1.15 (28.3.95)

        @{b}*@{ub} instead of printing 0% in the table UMSMailStat now prints the
          decimal-point and the first digit of the fraction-part: .5%
          instead of 0% (as requested by Luc Gibert)

        @{b}*@{ub} CLI-Usage now completely conforming the login-guide.

     v1.14 (14.3.95)

        @{b}*@{ub} the defaults for MaxUsers and MaxSubject are now read from the
          ums.config-variables @{"UMSMailStat.MaxUsers" Link "UMSMailStat.MaxUsers"} and
          @{"UMSMailStat.MaxSubjects" Link "UMSMailStat.MaxSubjects"}.  Only if these do not exist,
          UMSMailStat will fall back to its hardcoded values.

     v1.13 (25.2.95)

        @{b}*@{ub} new @{"CDATE" Link "CDATE"}-Option. Using this the messages will be selected by
          their creation-date instead of their import-date. This option
          is only available with an UMSServer v11.22+, with v10 this option has no effect.

     v1.12 (23.2.95)

        @{b}*@{ub} bumped revision number: the last public release (v1.11)
          contained the 1.09 binary :-( (Thanks to Matthias Scheler for
          the hint)

     v1.11 (13.2.95)

        @{b}*@{ub} if two or more authors/subjects have the same ranking (see
          v1.10) they will be printed in alphabetical order.

        @{b}*@{ub} break-handling removed, could lead into bad crashes :-(

        @{b}*@{ub} some layoutchanges to the documentation

     v1.10 (11.2.95)

        @{b}*@{ub} if two or more authors/subjects have the same amount of
          messages *and* bytes they will now have the same ranking.

        @{b}*@{ub} RB-shortcut for @{"REALBYTES" Link "REALBYTES"}

     v1.09 (15.1.95)

        @{b}*@{ub} cursor will now be switched off after the commandline has
          been parsed (requested by Christoph Viethen)

        @{b}*@{ub} some UMS-called have not been checked for errors.

        @{b}*@{ub} @{"REALBYTES" Link "REALBYTES"} option to get more accurate byte results.

     v1.08 (7.11.94)

        @{b}*@{ub} changed directory-structure of the distribution to fit Stefan
          Becker's guidelines

        @{b}*@{ub} revised the documentation

        @{b}*@{ub} @{"GROUP" Link "GROUP"} "" didn't state that the statistics were about the
          personal mail

        @{b}*@{ub} changed cursorswitching a bit

     v1.07 (3.11.94)

        @{b}*@{ub} memorymanagement now using memorypools, reducing
          fragmentation of mainmemory.

        @{b}*@{ub} lokalization with OS 2.1+, so the keyword ENGLISH is not
          needed anymore.

     v1.06 (9.4.94)

        @{b}*@{ub} MS can now be used for @{"MAXSUBJECTS" Link "MAXSUBJECTS"}, MU for @{"MAXUSERS" Link "MAXUSERS"}.

        @{b}*@{ub} some changes in the docs.

     v1.05 (20.1.94)

        @{b}*@{ub} discovered a very nasty bug, occuring with entries (subject
          or name) >= 25 chars, making the whole statistics unreliable.
          Fixed!

        @{b}*@{ub} scanning-speed slightly increased.

     v1.04 (13.1.94)

        @{b}*@{ub} changed the period-calculation again. @{"DAYS" Link "DATE & DAYS"} now really states
          who many days are considered in the stats, so @{"DAYS" Link "DATE & DAYS"}=7 really
          means "the last week" or "the week after (and including)
          @{"DATE" Link "DATE & DAYS"}. Why did I consider the other way to calculate the
          period to be more logical?!? :-)

     v1.03 (11.1.94)

        @{b}*@{ub} Happy New Year :-)

        @{b}*@{ub} removed a bug that appeared when specifying @{"DATE" Link "DATE & DAYS"} and @{"DAYS" Link "DATE & DAYS"}:
          the end of that period was at time 00:00:00 and not at time
          23:59:59, in fact a whole day of the period was missing (as
          if you would have specified @{"DAYS" Link "DATE & DAYS"}-1)

     v1.02 (19.12.93)

        @{b}*@{ub} @{"GROUP" Link "GROUP"} can now also be a pattern: all groups matching this
          pattern are taken into the stats.

     v1.01 (9.12.93)

        @{b}*@{ub} little "bugs" in the docs removed... ;-)

     v1.00 (8.12.93)

        @{b}*@{ub} first public release

@EndNode

